r, imo</p>","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-05-28T20:36:51.436Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":77,"readers_count":76,"score":15.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":466977,"topic_slug":"creating-a-demo-mode-for-our-robot-generichid-issues","display_username":"Tim Winters","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":62962,"username":"Paraduks","name":"Sam","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/ea5d25/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":19820,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"78 AIR Strike Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/creating-a-demo-mode-for-our-robot-generichid-issues/466977/11","custom_user_title":"78 AIR Strike Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3392917,"name":"","username":"w1zxrd","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/w1zxrd/{size}/246745_2.png","created_at":"2024-05-28T20:38:23.671Z","cooked":"<p>A team member who was on a team last year and the year before (we’re a rookie team, the team member is the only one with any <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> experience) says that it’s stressful, and also this allows our control team member to put in some corrective actions if the robot is moving dangerously.</p>","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-05-28T20:38:23.671Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":75,"readers_count":74,"score":20.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":466977,"topic_slug":"creating-a-demo-mode-for-our-robot-generichid-issues","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":54656,"username":"PatMcN","name":"Patrick McNaughton","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/patmcn/{size}/191694_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63685,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"9644 Captain + Driver"},"post_url":"/t/creating-a-demo-mode-for-our-robot-generichid-issues/466977/12","custom_user_title":"9644 Captain + Driver","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3392919,"name":"Patrick McNaughton","username":"PatMcN","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/patmcn/{size}/191694_2.png","created_at":"2024-05-28T20:43:47.823Z","cooked":"<p>I can speak from experience that this does work well. 341 has been running Sparky’s Robot World for something like 11 or 12 years now. We have a field with a couple quidditch looking goals, and small robots often controlled by children shooting foam balls into the goals. We always have 1 person stationed per controller with an on/off switch for the robot for safety reasons. It’s not that stressful, in fact it has prevented many collisions between erratically controlled robots and students resetting the field. <s>As far as the corrective actions, with having a second controller, how would this work? Would inputs from the second controller only happen if the first one was disabled? I imagine the command scheduler would not be happy if you had 2 controllers controlling the same thing.</s> read the other responses more in depth, nvm for the second part</p>","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-05-28T20:45:45.257Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":12,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":77,"readers_count":76,"score":30.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":466977,"topic_slug":"creating-a-demo-mode-for-our-robot-generichid-issues","display_username":"Patrick McNaughton","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":63685,"username":"w1zxrd","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/w1zxrd/{size}/246745_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54656,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"341 | Co-Captain"},"post_url":"/t/creating-a-demo-mode-for-our-robot-generichid-issues/466977/13","custom_user_title":"341 | Co-Captain","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3393253,"name":"Eli Barnett","username":"Oblarg","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/oblarg/{size}/161674_2.png","created_at":"2024-05-29T16:38:27.593Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="Paraduks" data-post="4" data-topic="466977" data-full="true">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/ea5d25/48.png" class="avatar"> Paraduks:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>We have had issues with CommandXboxController in the past, because it has bugs that cause loop scheduler overruns. This is why we resorted to GenericHID.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>It’s more a possible footgun than a bug, and shouldn’t be something you encounter if you’re using the class the way it is intended.</p>
<p>For context: if you repeatedly call the trigger factories from periodic code, you will leak memory.  This should be fixed for 2025, but also there is no reason to ever do this in the first place.  If you need to poll the controller state imperatively, do it on the internal non-Command controller instance.</p>","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-05-29T16:41:02.319Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":65,"readers_count":64,"score":58.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":466977,"topic_slug":"creating-a-demo-mode-for-our-robot-generichid-issues","display_username":"Eli Barnett","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":12381,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Robot apartments! invisible suburbs! skeleton treasuries!"},"post_url":"/t/creating-a-demo-mode-for-our-robot-generichid-issues/466977/14","custom_user_title":"Robot apartments! invisible suburbs! skeleton treasuries!","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3639704,"name":"system","username":"system","avatar_template":"/uploads/default/original/4X/9/3/2/93234578e69f55873c63fc00fe2d0d85f23bce55.png","created_at":"2025-05-29T16:38:31.137Z","cooked":"<p>This topic was automatically closed 365 days after the last reply. New replies are no lon